  "text": "A similar analysis can be performed for a trapped system, where we now consider the two components a and b in identical and spatially separated harmonic traps. In particular equation [CITATION_1] of [CITATION_2] is very similar to (72) except that in [CITATION_3] of [CITATION_4] we have N χ instead of ρg in (72). Another difference is that the more general equation [CITATION_5] in [CITATION_6] that includes two and three-body losses besides one-body losses, is derived performing an approximation on the effective Hamiltonian: the constant loss rate approximation [25]",
